---
import Base from '../../layouts/Base.astro';
export const prerender = true;

const SITE_URL = 'https://agentrank-ai.com';
---

<Base
  title="Rate Limits — AgentRank API"
  description="AgentRank API rate limits. Free tier: 100 req/min per IP. Pro tier: 10,000 req/day per key. Enterprise: unlimited."
  keywords="AgentRank rate limits, API limits, request throttling"
  canonicalUrl={`${SITE_URL}/docs/rate-limits/`}
  activeTab="api"
>
  <div class="page-header">
    <div class="breadcrumb"><a href="/docs/">Docs</a> / Rate Limits</div>
    <h1>Rate Limits</h1>
    <p class="subtitle">Free tier limits by IP. Pro tier limits by API key. Enterprise is unlimited.</p>
  </div>

  <nav class="docs-nav">
    <a href="/docs/">Overview</a>
    <a href="/docs/quickstart/">Quick Start</a>
    <a href="/docs/authentication/">Auth</a>
    <a href="/docs/rate-limits/" class="active">Rate Limits</a>
    <a href="/docs/api/">API Reference</a>
    <a href="/docs/sdk/">SDK</a>
    <a href="/docs/embed/">Embed</a>
  </nav>

  <div class="divider"></div>

  <section class="method" id="tiers">
    <h2>Limits by tier</h2>
    <div class="limits-table">
      <div class="limits-row header-row">
        <span>Tier</span>
        <span>Limit</span>
        <span>Window</span>
        <span>Tracked by</span>
      </div>
      <div class="limits-row">
        <span class="tier-badge free">Free (v1)</span>
        <span class="limit-val">100 requests</span>
        <span>Per minute</span>
        <span class="tracked-by">IP address</span>
      </div>
      <div class="limits-row">
        <span class="tier-badge pro">Pro (v2)</span>
        <span class="limit-val">10,000 requests</span>
        <span>Per day (UTC)</span>
        <span class="tracked-by">API key</span>
      </div>
      <div class="limits-row">
        <span class="tier-badge enterprise">Enterprise (v2)</span>
        <span class="limit-val">Unlimited</span>
        <span>—</span>
        <span class="tracked-by">API key</span>
      </div>
    </div>
    <p>The free tier window resets every minute. The Pro daily limit resets at <strong>00:00 UTC</strong>.</p>
  </section>

  <div class="divider"></div>

  <section class="method" id="headers">
    <h2>Rate limit headers</h2>
    <p>Every API response includes headers so you can track your usage:</p>
    <div class="header-table">
      <div class="header-row hdr">
        <span>Header</span>
        <span>Description</span>
        <span>Example</span>
      </div>
      <div class="header-row">
        <code>X-RateLimit-Limit</code>
        <span>Max requests for this window</span>
        <code>100</code>
      </div>
      <div class="header-row">
        <code>X-RateLimit-Remaining</code>
        <span>Requests remaining this window</span>
        <code>87</code>
      </div>
      <div class="header-row">
        <code>X-RateLimit-Reset</code>
        <span>ISO timestamp when window resets</span>
        <code>2026-03-18T05:12:59.999Z</code>
      </div>
      <div class="header-row">
        <code>X-API-Key-Tier</code>
        <span>Your key tier (Pro only)</span>
        <code>pro</code>
      </div>
    </div>
    <p>Enterprise keys do not include <code>X-RateLimit-*</code> headers (no limit to track).</p>
  </section>

  <div class="divider"></div>

  <section class="method" id="429">
    <h2>Handling 429 responses</h2>
    <p>When you hit the limit, the API returns <strong>HTTP 429</strong> with a JSON error body:</p>
    <div class="response-block">
      <div class="code-label">JSON</div>
      <pre class="response-code">{`{
  "error": "Rate limit exceeded. Max 100 requests per minute."
}`}</pre>
    </div>
    <p>For <strong>free tier</strong> (per-minute): wait until the next minute boundary (<code>X-RateLimit-Reset</code>).</p>
    <p>For <strong>Pro tier</strong> (per-day): limit resets at 00:00 UTC, or <a href="/pricing/">upgrade to Enterprise</a> for unlimited access.</p>

    <h3>Retry logic</h3>
    <div class="code-block-wrap">
      <div class="code-label">TS</div>
      <pre class="code-block multiline">{`async function fetchWithRetry(url: string, key?: string) {
  const headers = key ? { Authorization: \`Bearer \${key}\` } : {};
  const res = await fetch(url, { headers });

  if (res.status === 429) {
    const reset = res.headers.get('X-RateLimit-Reset');
    const wait = reset
      ? Math.max(0, new Date(reset).getTime() - Date.now())
      : 60_000;
    await new Promise(r => setTimeout(r, wait + 100));
    return fetch(url, { headers });
  }

  return res;
}`}</pre>
      <button class="copy-btn" data-copy={`async function fetchWithRetry(url: string, key?: string) {\n  const headers = key ? { Authorization: \`Bearer \${key}\` } : {};\n  const res = await fetch(url, { headers });\n\n  if (res.status === 429) {\n    const reset = res.headers.get('X-RateLimit-Reset');\n    const wait = reset\n      ? Math.max(0, new Date(reset).getTime() - Date.now())\n      : 60_000;\n    await new Promise(r => setTimeout(r, wait + 100));\n    return fetch(url, { headers });\n  }\n\n  return res;\n}`}>Copy</button>
    </div>
  </section>

  <div class="divider"></div>

  <section class="method" id="tips">
    <h2>Tips for staying under limits</h2>
    <ul class="info-list">
      <li>Cache responses on your side. Tool scores update once daily — caching for 1 hour loses nothing.</li>
      <li>Use the <strong>batch endpoint</strong> (<code>POST /api/v2/batch</code>) to fetch up to 50 tools in one request instead of 50 separate calls. Pro only.</li>
      <li>Use <code>limit</code> and <code>offset</code> for pagination rather than fetching everything at once.</li>
      <li>If you're building an integration that will exceed 10,000 req/day, <a href="mailto:api@agentrank-ai.com">contact us</a> about Enterprise pricing.</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <script>
    document.querySelectorAll<HTMLButtonElement>('.copy-btn').forEach(btn => {
      btn.addEventListener('click', () => {
        const text = btn.dataset.copy || btn.previousElementSibling?.textContent || '';
        if (!text) return;
        navigator.clipboard.writeText(text.trim()).then(() => {
          const orig = btn.textContent;
          btn.textContent = 'Copied!';
          setTimeout(() => { btn.textContent = orig; }, 2000);
        });
      });
    });
  </script>
</Base>

<style>
  .page-header { margin-bottom: 1.5rem; }

  .breadcrumb { font-size: 0.75rem; color: var(--text-muted); margin-bottom: 0.5rem; }
  .breadcrumb a { color: var(--text-muted); text-decoration: none; }
  .breadcrumb a:hover { color: var(--accent); }

  h1 { font-size: 1.5rem; font-weight: 700; margin-bottom: 0.5rem; }
  .subtitle { color: var(--text-muted); font-size: 0.88rem; }

  .docs-nav {
    display: flex;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
    gap: 0.25rem;
  }

  .docs-nav a {
    font-size: 0.78rem;
    color: var(--text-muted);
    text-decoration: none;
    padding: 0.25rem 0.6rem;
    border: 1px solid var(--border);
    border-radius: 3px;
    background: var(--bg-surface);
    transition: color 0.15s, border-color 0.15s;
  }

  .docs-nav a:hover { color: var(--text); text-decoration: none; }
  .docs-nav a.active { color: var(--accent); border-color: var(--accent); font-weight: 600; }

  .divider { border-top: 1px solid var(--border); margin: 2rem 0; }

  .method { margin-bottom: 0.5rem; }
  h2 { font-size: 1rem; font-weight: 700; margin-bottom: 0.75rem; }
  h3 { font-size: 0.88rem; font-weight: 700; margin: 1rem 0 0.5rem; color: var(--text); }

  p {
    font-size: 0.85rem;
    color: var(--text-muted);
    margin-bottom: 0.6rem;
    line-height: 1.5;
  }

  p code {
    background: var(--bg-surface);
    padding: 0.1rem 0.3rem;
    border-radius: 2px;
    font-size: 0.7rem;
    color: var(--text);
  }

  strong { color: var(--text); }

  .limits-table {
    border: 1px solid var(--border);
    border-radius: 4px;
    overflow: hidden;
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
  }

  .limits-row {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 9rem 8rem 8rem 1fr;
    gap: 0.75rem;
    align-items: center;
    padding: 0.5rem 0.75rem;
    font-size: 0.78rem;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border);
    color: var(--text-muted);
  }

  .limits-row:last-child { border-bottom: none; }

  .header-row {
    font-size: 0.65rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    color: var(--text-muted);
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.4px;
    background: var(--bg-surface);
  }

  .tier-badge {
    font-size: 0.72rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    padding: 0.1rem 0.4rem;
    border-radius: 3px;
    display: inline-block;
  }

  .tier-badge.free { background: rgba(34, 197, 94, 0.1); color: var(--accent); border: 1px solid rgba(34, 197, 94, 0.3); }
  .tier-badge.pro { background: rgba(96, 165, 250, 0.1); color: #60a5fa; border: 1px solid rgba(96, 165, 250, 0.3); }
  .tier-badge.enterprise { background: rgba(251, 191, 36, 0.1); color: #fbbf24; border: 1px solid rgba(251, 191, 36, 0.3); }

  .limit-val { font-weight: 600; color: var(--text); }
  .tracked-by { color: var(--text-muted); }

  .header-table {
    border: 1px solid var(--border);
    border-radius: 4px;
    overflow: hidden;
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
  }

  .header-row {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 14rem 1fr 10rem;
    gap: 0.75rem;
    align-items: center;
    padding: 0.45rem 0.75rem;
    font-size: 0.78rem;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border);
    color: var(--text-muted);
  }

  .header-row.hdr {
    font-size: 0.65rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.4px;
    background: var(--bg-surface);
  }

  .header-row:last-child { border-bottom: none; }

  .header-row code {
    font-size: 0.7rem;
    color: var(--accent);
    background: none;
    font-family: ui-monospace, 'Cascadia Code', 'Source Code Pro', monospace;
  }

  .header-row span { color: var(--text-muted); }

  .response-block {
    display: flex;
    align-items: flex-start;
    gap: 0.5rem;
    background: var(--bg);
    border: 1px solid var(--border);
    border-radius: 4px;
    padding: 0.6rem 0.75rem;
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
  }

  .code-label {
    font-size: 0.65rem;
    color: var(--text-muted);
    font-weight: 600;
    flex-shrink: 0;
    padding-top: 2px;
    width: 3rem;
  }

  .response-code {
    flex: 1;
    font-size: 0.7rem;
    color: var(--text-muted);
    white-space: pre;
    font-family: ui-monospace, 'Cascadia Code', 'Source Code Pro', monospace;
    background: none;
    border: none;
    margin: 0;
    padding: 0;
  }

  .code-block-wrap {
    display: flex;
    align-items: flex-start;
    gap: 0.5rem;
    background: var(--bg-surface);
    border: 1px solid var(--border);
    border-radius: 4px;
    padding: 0.6rem 0.75rem;
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
  }

  .code-block {
    flex: 1;
    font-size: 0.72rem;
    color: var(--text);
    overflow: hidden;
    text-overflow: ellipsis;
    white-space: nowrap;
    font-family: ui-monospace, 'Cascadia Code', 'Source Code Pro', monospace;
    background: none;
    border: none;
    margin: 0;
    padding: 0;
  }

  .code-block.multiline {
    white-space: pre;
    overflow-x: auto;
    text-overflow: unset;
  }

  .copy-btn {
    background: var(--bg);
    border: 1px solid var(--border);
    border-radius: 3px;
    padding: 0.2rem 0.45rem;
    font-size: 0.65rem;
    cursor: pointer;
    color: var(--text-muted);
    font-family: inherit;
    flex-shrink: 0;
    white-space: nowrap;
    align-self: flex-start;
  }

  .copy-btn:hover { border-color: var(--accent); color: var(--accent); }

  .info-list {
    list-style: none;
    padding: 0;
    margin: 0;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 0.4rem;
  }

  .info-list li {
    font-size: 0.82rem;
    color: var(--text-muted);
    padding-left: 1rem;
    position: relative;
    line-height: 1.5;
  }

  .info-list li::before {
    content: '·';
    position: absolute;
    left: 0;
    color: var(--accent);
  }

  .info-list li code {
    background: var(--bg-surface);
    padding: 0.1rem 0.3rem;
    border-radius: 2px;
    font-size: 0.7rem;
    color: var(--text);
  }

  @media (max-width: 600px) {
    .limits-row { grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr; }
    .limits-row > :nth-child(3), .limits-row > :nth-child(4) { display: none; }
    .header-row { grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr; }
    .header-row > :nth-child(3) { display: none; }
  }
</style>
